## Phase 3: User Story 1 - Automatic Tab Assignment on Session Creation (Priority: P1) 🎯 MVP

**Goal**: Sessions automatically bind to the active browser tab on creation, eliminating manual tab selection for 95% of use cases

**Independent Test**: Create a new session while a browser tab is active. Verify session.getTabId() returns the active tab's ID. Create session with no active tabs and verify tabId = -1.

### Implementation for User Story 1

- [ ] T035 [US1] Add active tab detection logic to Session constructor in src/core/Session.ts using chrome.tabs.query({active: true, currentWindow: true})
- [ ] T036 [US1] Update Session constructor to call TabManager.bindTabToSession() if active tab found in src/core/Session.ts
- [ ] T037 [US1] Update Session constructor to set sessionState.tabId to active tab ID if binding succeeds in src/core/Session.ts
- [ ] T038 [US1] Update Session constructor to set sessionState.tabId to -1 if no active tab found in src/core/Session.ts
- [ ] T039 [US1] Add error handling for active tab binding failures in Session constructor in src/core/Session.ts

### Tests for User Story 1

- [ ] T040 [P] [US1] Add test for session binding to active tab in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts (Given active tab 123, When session created, Then tabId = 123)
- [ ] T041 [P] [US1] Add test for session with no active tab in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts (Given no active tabs, When session created, Then tabId = -1)
- [ ] T042 [P] [US1] Add test for multiple windows scenario in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts (Given multiple windows with active tabs, When session created, Then binds to focused window's active tab)
- [ ] T043 [P] [US1] Update contract tests in tests/contract/tab-binding.contract.test.ts to verify automatic binding behavior
- [ ] T044 [US1] Verify all User Story 1 tests pass: npm test -- tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts

**Checkpoint**: User Story 1 complete - sessions automatically bind to active tabs, independently testable

