## Phase 4: User Story 2 - Automatic Tab Creation on First Message (Priority: P1) 🎯 MVP

**Goal**: Automatically create new tabs when users send messages to sessions with tabId = -1, ensuring agents always have a working context

**Independent Test**: Create session with tabId = -1, send a message, verify chrome.tabs.create() was called with about:blank and tabId updated before agent processing begins.

### Implementation for User Story 2

- [ ] T045 [US2] Add tab creation check to message submission handler (submitMessage or equivalent) in src/core/BrowserxAgent.ts or src/core/Session.ts
- [ ] T046 [US2] Call TabManager.createAndBindTab() with about:blank URL when tabId = -1 in message handler
- [ ] T047 [US2] Update session's tabId after successful tab creation in message handler
- [ ] T048 [US2] Add error handling for tab creation failures (show error, prevent message submission) in message handler
- [ ] T049 [US2] Verify new tab is added to "browserx" group (already handled by TabManager.createAndBindTab from T022)

### Tests for User Story 2

- [ ] T050 [P] [US2] Add test for automatic tab creation on message submission in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts (Given tabId = -1, When user sends message, Then tab created with about:blank)
- [ ] T051 [P] [US2] Add test for tab binding after creation in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts (verify session.getTabId() returns new tab ID)
- [ ] T052 [P] [US2] Add test for tab creation failure handling in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts (Given tab creation fails, Then error shown, message not sent)
- [ ] T053 [P] [US2] Add test for tab group membership in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts (verify new tab belongs to "browserx" group)
- [ ] T054 [US2] Verify all User Story 2 tests pass: npm test -- tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts

**Checkpoint**: User Story 2 complete - automatic tab creation on first message, independently testable

