## Phase 6: User Story 4 - Unified Tab Group Management (Priority: P2)

**Goal**: All tabs used by BrowserX agents appear in a single "browserx" tab group for easy visual identification

**Why out of sequence**: Core grouping logic was implemented in Phase 2 (T014-T022). This phase adds edge case handling and verification.

**Independent Test**: Create multiple sessions with different tabs, verify all belong to "browserx" tab group with blue color. Restart browser and verify group reused.

### Edge Case Handling for User Story 4

- [ ] T060 [US4] Add logic to handle manually deleted "browserx" group (recreate on next binding) in TabManager.bindTabToSession() in src/core/TabManager.ts
- [ ] T061 [US4] Update TabManager.initialize() to query for existing "browserx" group and reuse if found in src/core/TabManager.ts
- [ ] T062 [US4] Ensure group color remains "blue" even if user changes it (reset on initialization) in src/core/TabManager.ts

### Tests for User Story 4

- [ ] T063 [P] [US4] Add test for creating "browserx" group on first tab binding in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts
- [ ] T064 [P] [US4] Add test for reusing existing "browserx" group in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts
- [ ] T065 [P] [US4] Add test for recreating group after manual deletion in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts
- [ ] T066 [P] [US4] Add test for browser restart scenario (group reused) in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts
- [ ] T067 [P] [US4] Add test verifying all session tabs belong to same group in tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts
- [ ] T068 [US4] Verify all User Story 4 tests pass: npm test -- tests/integration/session-tab-lifecycle.test.ts

**Checkpoint**: User Story 4 complete - unified tab group management with edge cases handled

