## Dependencies & Execution Order

### Phase Dependencies

- **Setup (Phase 1)**: No dependencies - can start immediately
- **Foundational (Phase 2)**: Depends on Setup (Phase 1) completion - BLOCKS all user stories
- **User Stories (Phases 3-8)**: All depend on Foundational (Phase 2) completion
  - User Story 1 (Phase 3): Can start immediately after Phase 2
  - User Story 2 (Phase 4): Can start immediately after Phase 2
  - User Story 5 (Phase 5): Verification only, foundational work done in Phase 2
  - User Story 4 (Phase 6): Edge cases, core work done in Phase 2
  - User Story 6 (Phase 7): Can start immediately after Phase 2
  - User Story 3 (Phase 8): Depends on User Story 6 (Phase 7) for MessageInput component
- **Polish (Phase 9)**: Depends on all user stories being complete

### User Story Dependencies

- **User Story 1 (P1) - Automatic Tab Assignment**: Independent after Foundational
- **User Story 2 (P1) - Automatic Tab Creation**: Independent after Foundational, can run parallel with US1
- **User Story 5 (P3) - Service Worker Init**: Completed in Foundational, verification phase
- **User Story 4 (P2) - Tab Group Management**: Core completed in Foundational, edge cases independent
- **User Story 6 (P3) - MessageInput Component**: Independent after Foundational
- **User Story 3 (P2) - Manual Tab Selection**: Depends on User Story 6 (MessageInput must exist)

### Critical Path (Minimum to MVP)

For fastest path to MVP with P1 stories only:

1. Phase 1: Setup (T001-T013) → ~1-2 hours
2. Phase 2: Foundational (T014-T034) → ~4-6 hours
3. Phase 3: User Story 1 (T035-T044) → ~2-3 hours
4. Phase 4: User Story 2 (T045-T054) → ~2-3 hours
5. Phase 9: Essential polish (T106-T126) → ~2-3 hours

**MVP Total**: ~11-17 hours for P1 stories (automatic tab management)

### Within Each User Story

- Tests can run in parallel (marked [P])
- Implementation tasks may have dependencies (not all marked [P])
- Story complete before moving to next priority (recommended, not required)

### Parallel Opportunities

**Setup Phase (Phase 1)**:
- T003-T006: Import updates in different files can run in parallel
- T009-T011: Test file updates can run in parallel

**Foundational Phase (Phase 2)**:
- T014-T019: TabGroupManager method copying can run in parallel
- T023-T025: Test file updates can run in parallel
- T031-T032: Cleanup tasks can run in parallel

**User Story 1 (Phase 3)**:
- T040-T043: All test additions can run in parallel

**User Story 2 (Phase 4)**:
- T050-T053: All test additions can run in parallel

**User Story 4 (Phase 6)**:
- T063-T067: All test additions can run in parallel

**User Story 6 (Phase 7)**:
- T077-T080: All test creations can run in parallel

**User Story 3 (Phase 8)**:
- T097-T103: All test additions can run in parallel

**Polish Phase (Phase 9)**:
- T106-T108: Tool exclusion tasks can run in parallel with other polish tasks
- T109-T112: Edge case handling can run in parallel
- T113-T116: Integration test updates can run in parallel
- T117-T119: Performance tests can run in parallel
- T120-T122: Documentation cleanup can run in parallel

